rComments: Been my main man ever since CCT109 and as my TA for CCT110. I will admit he's become a far harder marker this year compared to last although I figure he may have just had a bad semester. Looking forward to having him again sometime
funny guy, makes course concepts easy to learn, approachable as well, clear grading, although he takes a while to answer emails, recommend just asking him after class!

Guys, I sincerely do not understand how you could not like Ryan. He's one of the chillest profs I've had! Amazing person, explains well, humorous,non-toxic, great lectures, posts slides, quick markings and soft on marking the exam. Just finished CCT109 with him - AMAZING bird course.
Not the worst, but certainly not the best. Doesn't seem to care about engaging or helping students.

Marking takes forever to be returned, always a week or 2 after other TAs. Does not really connect with students. Marking is a bit tough. The worst thing is that he does not really seem to care for the student or try to help. Answers to questions are very condescending. Overall, regret taking his class., and will definitely avoid taking his classes.

Ryan demonstrates that he decently understands course content. However, his marking, tutorial participation and instructions/directions can be very painful to deal with. The negative reputation comments that were mentioned by previous students of his tutorials was evident throughout the semester. Very tough marker and sometimes very ignorant.
